lenders.loan_because:
I KADA Contemporary Dance Company was formed in September 2011 in New York City. The company name "KADA" stands for Korean American Dance Association. We are a contemporary dance company focusing on cultural exchange through the arts. I KADA Contemporary Dance Company is to establish a dance school and a dance company to unite people and cultures. I KADA Contemporary Dance Company provides the following services such as the Annual Company Show, Workshop and Dance Agency which is helping international students integrate into American society by finding dance schools and housing, preparing visa interviews, English lessons, opening bank accounts, dance auditions, consultations, etc. Also I KADA will give dancers an opportunity to participate in the annual I KADA Contemporary Dance Company shows and festivals. Unlike other dance schools, I KADA has been doing contemporary dance shows since 2011 and has presented an international festival called KoDaFe in NYC since 2013. The festival has grown so much since it's beginning. This festival can definitely promote our dance school business. 

I KADA Dance Company has a wide range of potential clients and customers. People of different cultures and ages are welcome to participate in our services and everyone is invited to enjoy our performances. The main group we are targeting is professional / international dancers. We are a specialized company focusing on a niche market, which are primarily Korean, Korean-American and international clients. We are also focused on grooming young talent to grow within our system; therefore the youth are also one of our target markets. 

There are a wide variety of dance schools and studios in New York City. When measuring direct competition there are no other dance schools focusing on dance for Korean and American exchange. Carving out this niche we will be pioneers in the industry. There has been a recent influx of Koreans coming to America; now is the perfect time to develop this business. Spreading Korean culture into American society will be a big challenge but at the same time with our specific designed cultural exchange program, we can further meet the needs of our clients. 

The plan for I KADA is to develop and expand the dance company and services. This will include having my own dance school/studio and growing the festivals and shows. I am very proud of Korean culture and history and through the arts, more specifically dance I can share and express my passion to the world.
lenders.occupational_info: Hi my name is Mee Jung. I was born and raised in Seoul, Korea. As the center of Korea, Seoul has served as the country's capital for 600 years. Growing up in Seoul was confusing at times. I feel like most people and the culture are very conservative for me. I am more of a liberated person. I had broad visions about my dreams. Dance was my passion and vehicle to study abroad. Luckily I was able to perform with famous dancers and choreographers when I was in Korea. Through all my experiences I have been able to develop my interest in dance and I decided to come to America to pursue my dreams. I first came to Seattle in 2005 and since 2006 I have been living and working in New York City. In 2011 I began to make my dream become a reality by starting my dance company called I KADA Contemporary Dance Company. My dream is to develop and grow my dance company and have my own dance school/studio. I am sure all my experiences will help me in my future career. I also have taught students since 2000 back in Korea. I enjoyed and loved teaching dance and share my passion with people. My students loved my classes and my boss asked me to run the business with her. I was teaching only 1 or 2days a week at the beginning but my classes were getting bigger and my boss asked me to teach the classes 5 days a week and directed/ choreographed for all the showcases at the dance school in Korea. As a dancer, choreographer and a teacher, I have really enjoyed my work and all my experiences helped me how to commit other people and be an inspiration to others.
